For brief building instructions, see INSTALL.

Developers environment
======================

You need the following software:

* CMake
    Debian: "cmake"
    http://packages.debian.org/sid/cmake
    
* pkg-config
    Debian: "pkg-config"
    http://packages.debian.org/sid/pkg-config
    
* Qt4 libraries
    Debian: "libqt4-dev"
    http://packages.debian.org/sid/libqt4-dev
    
* KDE4 SDK and libraries
    Debian: "kdesdk", "kdelibs5-dev"
    http://packages.debian.org/sid/kdesdk
    http://packages.debian.org/sid/kdelibs5-dev

* ALSA library
    Debian package: "libasound2-dev"
    http://packages.debian.org/sid/libasound2-dev

* DBus-1 library
    Debian package: "libdbus-1-dev"
    http://packages.debian.org/sid/libdbus-1-dev

Getting the development sources
===============================

Compiling and hacking the CVS sources is a bit different compared to the
distribution tarball. You can get the latest sources either using a sourceforge
user account, or the anonymous user (with read only rights). The CVS client  
documentation for SourceForge users is available at
http://sourceforge.net/apps/trac/sourceforge/wiki/CVS%20client%20instructions

1. Check out the module aseqmm from the CVS repository.
        Host: kmetronome.cvs.sourceforge.net
        Path: /cvsroot/kmetronome
        Module: aseqmm

example:
$ cvs -z3 -d:pserver:anonymous@kmetronome.cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/kmetronome checkout -P aseqmm  

2. Check out the module kmidimon from the CVS repository.
        Host: kmetronome.cvs.sourceforge.net
        Path: /cvsroot/kmetronome
        Module: kmidimon

example:
$ cvs -z3 -d:pserver:anonymous@kmetronome.cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/kmetronome checkout -P kmidimon  

3. Create the links for 'aseqmm' in the kmidimon directory.
$ cd kmidimon
$ ./link-aseqmm

The module 'aseqmm' is also used by other projects in a similar way. 
It will become an independent shared library some future day.

4. Configure and compile

$ cmake . -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=debug -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=`kde4-config --prefix`
$ make VERBOSE=1

5. Hack and enjoy!
